<li>    For more information, see Thierer and Barry, "How the Telecom Bill Gives Away $70 Billion in Family Tax Relief to the Broadcast Industry"; Adam D. Thierer, "The Great Taxpayer Rip-off of 1995," <I>Regulation</I>, No. 4 (1995), pp. 21-23; Thomas W. Hazlett, "Free the Airwaves," <I>The American Enterprise</I>, Vol. 7, No. 2 (March/April 1996), p. 71-72; Safire, "Stop the Giveaway"; Karen Kerrigan, "Hijacking the Broadcast Spectrum," <I>The Washington Times</I>, August 21, 1995, p. A18; "I-Way Detours," <I>The Wall Street Journal</I>, December 27, 1995, p. 10.<p>
