<p><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Although some 3 million Mexicans enter the U.S. illegally each year, about 2.7 million also return to Mexico. Net illegal immigration from Mexico has averaged about 300,000 persons annually in recent years. Illegal immigration must be controlled, but the U.S. is not being overwhelmed by a flood of illegal immigrants.
